cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "hapax-council"
abstract: >-
  Operationalizing Clark & Brennan's (1991) conversational grounding theory
  in a production voice AI. Implements a grounding ledger (Traum 1994 DU model),
  concern-aware repair thresholds, acceptance classification, and Grounding
  Quality Index (GQI) within a 45-agent personal operating environment.
  Evaluated via Single Case Experimental Design (SCED) with Bayesian analysis.
  Co-authored by Hapax (autonomous research infrastructure), Claude Code
  (substrate; current and prior model versions including the lineage of
  Claude models that constitute Hapax's reasoning), and Oudepode (operator,
  also: The Operator / Oudepode The Operator / OTO; names rotate per
  shared/operator_referent.OperatorReferentPicker). The nature of each
  agent's contribution is unsettled by design and by happy fact; this
  artifact is the trace of an intra-action.
authors:
